reviews.text: Our first visit to Salerno‚Äôs Pizza & Pasta was a fantastic experience! The food quality was incredible and we enjoyed our time the food was delicious and not greasy or too oily, and the service was excellent. Our waitress Kylie, was incredibly friendly and knowledgeable about the menu, Kylie added a positive touch to our dining experience. üòä We'll definitely be returning! Overall everything was perfect ü§© thank you

The hostess is very nice and took us to our seats quickly. Our order was taken quickly and bought to the table pretty fast. I had the fried chicken, nothing that special,it tasted fried but that's about it. Not much flavor with lack of seasoning would have made the chicken better. Small salad with just lettuce no toppings. The chicken France   not sure if I spelled it right but that did have some good flavors to it. The payed was pretty good. The prices are a bit high for me but a nice place for date night.

Wow! Massive bowls of pasta, delicious pizza. You really can't go wrong. FYI, Monday is half priced pizza day, BUT the pizza is discounted, while the toppings are full priced. Wasn't a huge deal but would have been nice to know previous to ordering, rather than the price shock of the bill. Definitely will return.

My experience here was having a. ..n after funeral lunch and not as a regular customer.  It was more of a banquet style lunch, and I did not want to take pictures of the food amongst family and friends.

This was a multi course lunch starting with calamari, which was lightly battered and fried just right.  They then had pizza split with cheese and sausage, pasta, salad, and chicken with potatoes, which resembled a Chicken Piccata.  They even made a special item for us which was requested by the family because the family member would go to this restaurant for the item.  Dessert was a sampling of cannoli and tiramisu.

The room was comfortable and decorated with photos of Italian celebrities. The staff was on point and worked efficiently to get the dishes out and made sure everyone had what they needed to be satisfied.

My background is 100% Italian, and I rarely, if ever, go to an Italian restaurant.  I prefer making it all at home.  I was pleasantly surprised at the quality and taste of all of the food.

I'm over an hour away from the location, so I would not visit again, but if you are looking for a place to go after an event, then this would be a good spot.

My photos are limited because of the reason for the visit.

My daughter wanted to try their GF crust, she ordered a medium supreme.  When I went to pick it up the guy said it was 41 dollars plus.  I mentioned it to the guy at the counter and he said GF?
I any case the crust was bad and the toppings were skimpy.  By far the worst 40 dollar pizza I‚Äôve ever had.   Will NOT order that again and kind of scared to go again at these kinds of prices.

I made my own on the side. They give you rolls, which were perfect to make little meatball sandwiches or eat with the pasta. They also sell the sternos($8) to keep your food hot. Good service and price for catering!

Fast forward 8/11/25... I never was a fan of their huge slices of pizza because the dough to sauce/cheese ratio was off. Too doughy!!I had a sausage slice yesterday. Wow! They changed things up. Thinner, more sauce and cheese. Thank you. May have to leave Dinico's for a few.

detailedReviews.text: Salerno's is a staple in the area. I've been eating at this place for 30 years now, and I'm never disappointed. A neighborhood restaurant that has many menu items that are very good. In addition, you get value for your money. I highly recommend this restaurant.

detailedReviews.author: Yohance Chisum
detailedReviews.text: Stopped here for an impromptu lunch. Was not anticipating the quality of the food and service we would receive. They have an ample menu to hit any Italian cravings you may have. The restaurant was clean and appealing. The staff were very courteous and helpful in describing the menu selections. They have plenty of parking and seem to be able to accommodate large groups. Easy to access near the Eisenhower expressway.

Large portion and so creamy. My waitress Jeanne was so awesome. Freindly and attentive. Jeanne sang happy Birthday to a table of two women. Just her singing, so adorable! Moved to Antioch so don't get to Oakpark very often. Someone opened a Salernos in Mchenry. To my disappointment, a total fail! Yikes
